    "If run every day on successively longer windows, the early-warning monitoring system (AE-VI) would require a total of 0.5 ± 0.03 Wh for the month.",
    "Since the inference GPU energy required by RF is still low (4.47 ± 0.32 Wh), a combined RF-AE system would only use 4.97 Wh over that period if run each day for a higher-resolution analysis.",
    "Meanwhile, the highercomplexity model requires significantly more inference energy under the same circumstances (MSI-ViT: 0.98 ± 0.07 kWh).",
    "However, this computational energy consumption pales in comparison to the wasted embodied energy from excess N application.",
    "Seeing that global NUE averages 46%, 5 our experimental scenario (with total average T1 tissue N 0.383 g  0.052), scaled to the same 10,000 heads of lettuce, would require 8.32 ± 1.13 kg N, of which 4.49 kg ± 0.61 N would be wasted as effluent."
